I. SOFTWARE COMPONENTS

You will find the following software packages:

Main algorithm)
- BASIS_Master.m: control the whole algorithm flow and distribute jobs
- BASIS_Worker.m: workers that receive individual parallelized job from Master
- User_Input.m: prepare system parameters to run BASIS_Master.m
- User_Input_Defaults.m: a backup copy of the defaulted system parameter values
- Run_Me.m: a dummy file to run the algorithm directly when all setup done

Supporting materials)
- Plot_Results.m: plotting the results of BASIS directly
- HANDBOOK.txt: overview of the algorithm structure and recent updates
- README.txt: this file
- AUTHORS: contains all author and contact information
- COPYING: legal terms for using this package

Example)
- Run_Me_Example.m: main code to run BASIS on the two given examples
- User_Input_Example.m: setup system parameters for the example
- Lik_Banana.m: a sample log-likelihood function for the banana example
- Lik_Gauss_3D.m: a sample log-likelihood function for the 3D Gaussian example


II. PREREQUISITES

- MATLAB with optimization and parallel package (this package uses parpool)


III. NOTES

Read HANDBOOK.txt for overview of the algorithm usage
Look into User_Input.m for the important parameters and their purpose

Ask for help, report any problems!: wust@ethz.ch 

